\subsection Overview

The V2-Fun package is a tool for computing fully developed channel flow using the v2-f turbulence model. 
This code was originally written as a final project for Dr. Chris Simmon's <em>Tools and Techniques of Computational Science</em> class 
and later updated for Dr. Robert Moser's <em>Turbulence</em> class, with the help of Clark Peterson, Tim Smith, and Sean Carney. 
The latest version of v2fun can be download <a href="http://users.ices.utexas.edu/~gopal/v2fun/v2fun.tar">here</a>. 
The code is written in C++ and makes use of the external libraries <a href="https://www.gnu.org/software/gsl/">GSL</a> and <a href="http://boost.org">BOOST</a>. 
To aid in usage and installation, please see the related pages:

